Class Pool<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.davidsoergel.dsutils.Pool<E>

  • public class Pool<E>
extends Object
    An object pool, to allow reusing objects that are expensive to instantiate.

    Should we use org.apache.commons.lang.Pool instead? Or that high-performance realtime library thing? Or nothing, because object pooling is now Considered Harmful?
